- Oh.

12
00:00:22.823 --> 00:00:24.925
Where. Dave? In your yard?

13
00:00:25.693 --> 00:00:27.461
And he parked here
yesterday. too.

14
00:00:27.561 --> 00:00:29.497
- Hmm.
- It's fine.

15
00:00:29.563 --> 00:00:31.999
I left a terse note
on his windshield.

16
00:00:32.900 --> 00:00:35.869
I can't understand
why you are not furious.

17
00:00:35.969 --> 00:00:37.638
'Cause if I left him a note.
it would say.

18
00:00:37.705 --> 00:00:40.841
"Sorry for smashing out
all your windows!"

19
00:00:40.908 --> 00:00:43.177
Calvin. can you help me
get out of here?

20
00:00:43.277 --> 00:00:45.213
- Okay. yeah.
- Excuse me. I'm right here.

21
00:00:46.647 --> 00:00:47.881
Okay. no. you know what?
You probably need to

22
00:00:47.981 --> 00:00:49.317
straighten it out
just a little bit first.

23
00:00:49.383 --> 00:00:51.085
and then. and then cut it.

24
00:00:51.185 --> 00:00:53.187
- No. no. no. cut it... to your left.
- Cut it which way?

25
00:00:53.287 --> 00:00:55.089
- To your left. Gemma. Go left-left.
- I would cut it to your right.

26
00:00:55.189 --> 00:00:56.957
No. do not cut it to your right.

27
00:00:57.057 --> 00:00:59.026
- Don't listen to me.
- You don't know what you're talking about.

28
00:00:59.127 --> 00:01:00.561
♪ Welcome to the block.
welcome to the neighborhood ♪

29
00:01:00.694 --> 00:01:02.062
♪ Welcome to the hood. ♪

30
00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:08.068
Hey. Dad.

31
00:01:08.169 --> 00:01:09.737
Do you know where
my birth certificate is?

32
00:01:09.837 --> 00:01:12.039
Oh. sure. Look in the glove box.

33
00:01:12.106 --> 00:01:13.441
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

34
00:01:13.574 --> 00:01:15.609
Oh. no. it's not!

35
00:01:16.377 --> 00:01:19.313
Marty. I haven't seen
your birth certificate

36
00:01:19.447 --> 00:01:21.249
since your mother
signed my name on it.

37
00:01:21.315 --> 00:01:24.551
Uh. that tracks.
but Courtney and I need it

38
00:01:24.618 --> 00:01:26.019
to get our marriage license.

39
00:01:26.120 --> 00:01:28.489
Aw. don't worry. Marty.
Of course I've got it.

40
00:01:28.589 --> 00:01:31.158
- but I'm gonna need it back.
- Why?

41
00:01:31.259 --> 00:01:33.161
'Cause you'll lose it.

42
00:01:34.094 --> 00:01:37.965
Mama. I'm about to be
a whole husband. okay?

43
00:01:38.765 --> 00:01:40.501
You know what. Marty?
You're right.

44
00:01:40.601 --> 00:01:43.304
After the wedding.
I'll give it to your wife.

45
00:01:44.305 --> 00:01:46.340
Come on. babe.
that's ridiculous.

46
00:01:46.473 --> 00:01:48.176
Is it? Okay.

47
00:01:48.309 --> 00:01:50.711
Well. Calvin.
where's your birth certificate?

48
00:01:50.811 --> 00:01:52.979
I don't know. You have it.

49
00:01:53.080 --> 00:01:54.247
Mm.

50
00:01:54.315 --> 00:01:56.184
See what I'm saying?

51
00:01:57.251 --> 00:01:59.152
I know I don't
say this enough...

52
00:02:00.521 --> 00:02:03.023
- but I love you.
- Okay. okay.

53
00:02:03.123 --> 00:02:05.359
David. you say it all the time.

54
00:02:05.493 --> 00:02:06.594
Ah. Gemma.

55
00:02:06.694 --> 00:02:09.463
- Oh. Dave. Are you okay?
- Yes.

56
00:02:09.562 --> 00:02:10.898
I'm alive. Oh. Calvin.

57
00:02:10.997 --> 00:02:13.301
No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

58
00:02:14.335 --> 00:02:15.936
What the hell is going on?

59
00:02:16.036 --> 00:02:19.006
I was running down Marengo.
w-working on my six-minute mile.

60
00:02:19.106 --> 00:02:22.276
when out of nowhere. one of
those food delivery robots

61
00:02:22.343 --> 00:02:24.845
came careening
down the sidewalk.

62
00:02:24.945 --> 00:02:27.014
totally out of control.

63
00:02:27.114 --> 00:02:28.382
I had to leap out of the way

64
00:02:28.482 --> 00:02:30.017
and almost stumbled
into traffic.

65
00:02:30.117 --> 00:02:31.319
But you're okay?

66
00:02:31.385 --> 00:02:35.155
Well. yes. thanks
to my catlike reflexes.

67
00:02:35.856 --> 00:02:37.925
Oh. my God.
and now I smell like you.

68
00:02:39.527 --> 00:02:42.663
But as I lay there.

69
00:02:42.763 --> 00:02:43.831
looking into the light...

70
00:02:43.930 --> 00:02:45.633
- Okay.
- What is he looking at?

71
00:02:45.699 --> 00:02:47.735
Okay.

72
00:02:47.835 --> 00:02:50.371
I realized
I almost made you a widow.

73
00:02:51.272 --> 00:02:53.641
Grover. a half an orphan.

74
00:02:54.508 --> 00:02:56.577
Is that the robot?

75
00:02:57.745 --> 00:02:59.747
Oh. dear God.

76
00:02:59.880 --> 00:03:02.350
It's coming back
to finish me off!

77
00:03:03.917 --> 00:03:05.419
Is this what...?

78
00:03:05.519 --> 00:03:07.054
- Uh. s... I'm-I'm sorry!
- Really? - Oh. really. Marty?

79
00:03:07.154 --> 00:03:09.089
I'm-I'm sorry! I'm sorry. Dave.

80
00:03:09.223 --> 00:03:11.425
Okay? I had a hankering
for chilaquiles.

81
00:03:12.693 --> 00:03:14.595
Where is my churro?

82
00:03:17.431 --> 00:03:19.533
162.

83
00:03:19.600 --> 00:03:21.602
- Age?
- 43.

84
00:03:21.702 --> 00:03:23.904
- Height?
- Six-one.

85
00:03:28.041 --> 00:03:29.243
Six foot.

86
00:03:32.079 --> 00:03:35.283
Five-11. final offer.

87
00:03:35.416 --> 00:03:37.285
Sir. this is not
for a dating app.

88
00:03:37.385 --> 00:03:40.087
I just work
for the insurance company.

89
00:03:40.888 --> 00:03:42.823
Dave. I know
yesterday was traumatic.

90
00:03:42.923 --> 00:03:44.525
but we already have
life insurance.

91
00:03:44.591 --> 00:03:45.926
But you can never have enough.

92
00:03:46.059 --> 00:03:48.095
Look. you don't realize
how fragile life is

93
00:03:48.195 --> 00:03:50.298
until you're almost killed
by a Decepticon.

94
00:03:50.430 --> 00:03:53.501
It was a rolling cooler
full of tacos.

95
00:03:54.602 --> 00:03:58.372
Regardless. I just want
to make sure that. God forbid.

96
00:03:58.472 --> 00:03:59.707
something happened to me.

97
00:03:59.807 --> 00:04:01.275
that you and Grover
are taken care of.

98
00:04:01.409 --> 00:04:04.412
Dave. stop. I hate thinking
about life without you.

99
00:04:04.478 --> 00:04:06.414
You have to be prepared.

100
00:04:06.514 --> 00:04:08.782
And just promise me
that you won't mourn forever.

101
00:04:08.882 --> 00:04:10.518
Join a widows'
grief support group.

102
00:04:10.618 --> 00:04:12.653
You know. move on.

103
00:04:12.786 --> 00:04:14.021
Enjoy life.

104
00:04:14.121 --> 00:04:16.856
You know. maybe...
even meet someone.

105
00:04:16.957 --> 00:04:20.793
Wh... Oh. God.
I can't imagine that.

106
00:04:20.894 --> 00:04:24.365
I wouldn't even be able to think
about dating for a year or two.

107
00:04:27.801 --> 00:04:30.137
- A year?
- Or two.

108
00:04:31.271 --> 00:04:33.073
Or five.

109
00:04:33.140 --> 00:04:35.142
No. No. no. no. You know what?

110
00:04:35.275 --> 00:04:37.445
I'm sorry.
It's what I want for you.

111
00:04:37.511 --> 00:04:40.180
You know. maybe you and your
widow friends plan a vacation.

112
00:04:40.314 --> 00:04:42.450
Go to. say. Greece.

113
00:04:42.550 --> 00:04:46.086
Hit up the clubs in Mykonos.
you meet a DJ named Stavros.

114
00:04:46.153 --> 00:04:47.821
He doesn't speak
much English. but.

115
00:04:47.921 --> 00:04:51.325
God knows. he doesn't have to.
not with that jawline.

116
00:04:53.060 --> 00:04:55.228
So you're telling me
we've had this stuff

117
00:04:55.329 --> 00:04:57.331
under our bed for 30 years?

118
00:04:57.465 --> 00:04:58.832
Just keep looking.

119
00:04:58.932 --> 00:05:01.001
The birth certificates
are in one of these.

120
00:05:01.101 --> 00:05:02.870
Come on. Tina. really?

121
00:05:02.970 --> 00:05:05.072
- Macaroni art.
- Oh. let me see.

122
00:05:05.172 --> 00:05:07.941
- A kindergarten graduation cap.
- Aw.

123
00:05:08.041 --> 00:05:09.343
Look at this.

124
00:05:09.443 --> 00:05:12.380
You know. you got a whole box
of hand turkeys.

125
00:05:12.480 --> 00:05:14.047
Oh.

126
00:05:14.147 --> 00:05:16.850
But you gonna throw away
my Jet "Beauty of the Weeks."

127
00:05:16.950 --> 00:05:19.420
My Jayne Kennedy.

128
00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:27.074
-== [ www.OpenSubtitles.org ] ==-

129
00:05:28.396 --> 00:05:31.198
O-Okay. uh. here we go.

130
00:05:31.298 --> 00:05:33.467
These are report cards. Ah.

131
00:05:33.534 --> 00:05:35.836
- Here go the birth certificates right here.
- Yes.

132
00:05:35.936 --> 00:05:37.871
There we go.

133
00:05:37.971 --> 00:05:40.073
What's this little envelope?

134
00:05:41.875 --> 00:05:43.877
What are these?

135
00:05:43.977 --> 00:05:47.648
Aw. that's their baby teeth.

136
00:05:47.748 --> 00:05:49.282
What?

137
00:05:51.318 --> 00:05:52.953
And you kept them? Why?

138
00:05:53.053 --> 00:05:56.490
'Cause I just like
to look at them sometimes.

139
00:05:56.557 --> 00:05:57.691
When?

140
00:05:57.791 --> 00:05:59.527
Just put 'em back
in the envelope. Calvin!

141
00:05:59.627 --> 00:06:02.229
No. no. no. no. no. no. no.
Tina. you know what?

142
00:06:02.329 --> 00:06:03.431
Enough is enough.

143
00:06:03.531 --> 00:06:04.932
All right. they're grown men.

144
00:06:05.065 --> 00:06:07.067
Let's just get rid
of all this stuff.

145
00:06:07.167 --> 00:06:09.937
No. I can't throw
their baby teeth away.

146
00:06:10.070 --> 00:06:12.540
You know what? I'll just
put them under the bed.

147
00:06:12.640 --> 00:06:14.341
No. you won't.

148
00:06:14.442 --> 00:06:16.243
I ain't sleeping
on no damn teeth.

149
00:06:18.979 --> 00:06:21.048
Sorry about the urine sample.

150
00:06:21.148 --> 00:06:22.450
You sure it's enough?

151
00:06:22.550 --> 00:06:24.117
It's fine.

152
00:06:25.152 --> 00:06:26.620
It's so weird.

153
00:06:26.720 --> 00:06:28.422
You know. at the movies.
I have to go. like. five times.

154
00:06:28.522 --> 00:06:29.890
Gemma. tell her. at the movies.

155
00:06:29.957 --> 00:06:32.426
- how many...
- Dave. she said it's fine.

156
00:06:34.361 --> 00:06:37.698
Blood pressure 155/90.

157
00:06:37.798 --> 00:06:39.933
What? That's high. right?

158
00:06:40.033 --> 00:06:41.268
Yeah. that's pretty high.

159
00:06:41.401 --> 00:06:43.437
Hold on. this makes no sense.
It's impossible.

160
00:06:43.571 --> 00:06:45.172
Well. hold on.

161
00:06:46.306 --> 00:06:48.141
Look. Look. I mean...

162
00:06:48.241 --> 00:06:49.943
I'm in good shape.
I mean...

163
00:06:50.043 --> 00:06:52.613
Sure. I can't always
make urine on demand.

164
00:06:52.746 --> 00:06:54.114
but...

165
00:06:54.214 --> 00:06:56.617
Dave. calm down.
We'll figure it out.

166
00:06:56.717 --> 00:06:58.652
No.
Look. I-I don't smoke.

167
00:06:58.786 --> 00:07:00.287
I... never used drugs.

168
00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:02.122
I mean. there was
that one Fourth of July

169
00:07:02.222 --> 00:07:04.958
that I did snort Pop Rocks.
but that's it.

170
00:07:08.328 --> 00:07:10.130
Hey. Calvin.

171
00:07:10.230 --> 00:07:11.665
Dave.

172
00:07:11.765 --> 00:07:14.034
I see that guy has your driveway
blocked in again.

173
00:07:14.134 --> 00:07:17.938
Can't believe your little note
didn't scare him straight.

174
00:07:18.038 --> 00:07:19.306
It might be my fault.

175
00:07:19.406 --> 00:07:20.608
You know.
he's probably a young guy.

176
00:07:20.707 --> 00:07:22.175
I don't think they read cursive.

177
00:07:24.011 --> 00:07:26.279
You know. and he moved
your garbage cans

178
00:07:26.379 --> 00:07:28.015
to make room for himself.

179
00:07:28.148 --> 00:07:30.350
You never touch
another man's cans.

180
00:07:31.351 --> 00:07:33.386
Look.

181
00:07:33.487 --> 00:07:35.489
It's not worth
getting upset about.

182
00:07:35.589 --> 00:07:38.692
Aw. gosh darn it.

183
00:07:38.792 --> 00:07:39.927
What's that?

184
00:07:40.027 --> 00:07:42.029
It's my wearable
blood pressure monitor.

185
00:07:42.129 --> 00:07:43.597
I'm trying to lower
my blood pressure

186
00:07:43.697 --> 00:07:46.299
or I'm gonna pay through
the nose for life insurance.

187
00:07:46.366 --> 00:07:48.769
You know...
I'm doing everything I can.

188
00:07:48.869 --> 00:07:51.539
I eat right. Exercise.

189
00:07:51.639 --> 00:07:54.041
I sleep well.
I take two naps a day.

190
00:07:54.174 --> 00:07:57.409
You know.
maybe I eat too much kale.

191
00:07:59.513 --> 00:08:01.114
I don't know
what to tell you. Dave.

192
00:08:01.181 --> 00:08:02.683
My blood pressure's
always normal.

193
00:08:02.816 --> 00:08:04.985
So jealous.

194
00:08:05.052 --> 00:08:06.453
I mean. you can't
compare yourself to me.

195
00:08:06.554 --> 00:08:09.489
I grew up in the '70s.
We grew up tough.

196
00:08:09.590 --> 00:08:12.693
No helmets. No seat belts.
No allergies.

197
00:08:14.027 --> 00:08:16.864
Pretty sure people in the '70s
had allergies.

198
00:08:18.465 --> 00:08:20.433
I didn't know any of them.

199
00:08:22.135 --> 00:08:24.304
Calvin said I should
get rid of this stuff.

200
00:08:24.404 --> 00:08:25.806
but it's really hard.

201
00:08:25.873 --> 00:08:27.908
I've been there.
It almost killed me last year

202
00:08:28.008 --> 00:08:31.612
when I finally got rid of
Grover's light-up potty.

203
00:08:33.981 --> 00:08:35.215
He's 14.

204
00:08:35.347 --> 00:08:37.384
You have a bag
of Malcolm's hair.

205
00:08:37.517 --> 00:08:40.888
Ooh. it was so curly.

206
00:08:41.722 --> 00:08:44.592
But once you do it. you'll feel
so good about yourself.

207
00:08:44.725 --> 00:08:46.459
- Yeah.
- Trust me.

208
00:08:46.560 --> 00:08:47.895
Like. what is this?

209
00:08:48.028 --> 00:08:51.164
Oh. Malcolm made this for me
for Mother's Day.

210
00:08:51.231 --> 00:08:52.566
But what is it?

211
00:08:52.700 --> 00:08:54.267
It's a...

212
00:08:54.367 --> 00:08:56.003
It's a paperweight.

213
00:08:56.069 --> 00:08:58.538
- There's two of them.
- Then they're bookends. Gemma.

214
00:08:58.606 --> 00:09:00.073
Okay.

215
00:09:01.008 --> 00:09:02.009
Hey. Mama.

216
00:09:02.075 --> 00:09:03.644
Oh. good. My babies are here.

217
00:09:03.744 --> 00:09:06.179
Okay. I've got
your birth certificates.

218
00:09:06.246 --> 00:09:08.949
your Social Security cards
and your passports.

219
00:09:09.082 --> 00:09:10.984
- Aw. thank you. Ma.
- Also.

220
00:09:11.084 --> 00:09:13.520
all of this is all yours now.

221
00:09:13.621 --> 00:09:16.089
- Oh.
- Oh. Okay. uh...

222
00:09:16.223 --> 00:09:17.891
- What is that. finger paintings?
- Mm.

223
00:09:17.991 --> 00:09:20.961
Yeah. we don't need any of that
stuff. You can just toss it.

224
00:09:21.762 --> 00:09:24.197
- So. you want me to die?
- No.

225
00:09:26.233 --> 00:09:28.301
This is your childhood.

226
00:09:28.435 --> 00:09:30.638
Well. no. come on. Mama.
a-a place mat

227
00:09:30.771 --> 00:09:32.840
from Gravy Jack's
is not our childhood.

228
00:09:32.940 --> 00:09:35.542
Aw. Look. you did the maze.

229
00:09:35.643 --> 00:09:37.945
Oh. Tina. honey.

230
00:09:38.078 --> 00:09:39.279
That is garbage.

231
00:09:39.412 --> 00:09:42.182
Oh. my God.
there's. like. ten of them.

232
00:09:43.216 --> 00:09:44.517
Oh. man. remember these?

233
00:09:44.618 --> 00:09:46.319
What? Muchigon cards?

234
00:09:46.453 --> 00:09:48.188
We used to get
so excited about these.

235
00:09:48.288 --> 00:09:51.324
Yeah. and now you're excited
to throw them out.

236
00:09:51.424 --> 00:09:52.860
Oh. man. Vampirax.

237
00:09:52.960 --> 00:09:54.728
Wereturtle. Pterodactyclops?

238
00:09:54.795 --> 00:09:57.564
That's the one
I got sent to detention for

239
00:09:57.665 --> 00:09:59.633
because I was showing my friends
in social studies.

240
00:09:59.767 --> 00:10:02.102
Ah. in your defense.
it was incredibly rare.

241
00:10:02.169 --> 00:10:03.436
Well. I couldn't believe
I had one.

242
00:10:03.536 --> 00:10:05.105
Wow. Marty. that's so cool.

243
00:10:05.172 --> 00:10:08.341
A one-eyed dino-bird card
that proves you're a virgin.

244
00:10:13.013 --> 00:10:16.549
Dave. the point of our team
meetings isn't to socialize.

245
00:10:16.650 --> 00:10:19.019
Okay. but all I did was ask

246
00:10:19.119 --> 00:10:21.254
that Brian guy
how his weekend was.

247
00:10:21.354 --> 00:10:23.490
That's an invasion of privacy.

248
00:10:23.590 --> 00:10:25.525
It's giving ick.

249
00:10:25.625 --> 00:10:27.427
I-I'm sorry. "ick"?

250
00:10:27.494 --> 00:10:31.231
Wh-What is. what is "ick"
and how can it be given?

